It is also called method Overloading
In a class we have same method name with different parameters is called method overloading.
Either one or more parameters should be differents.
If a return type is different and have same method name and parameters then it will not consider as method overloading.
______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

When we use:
When we want same method name but data types should be different that time method overloading is used.
______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
Features:
More readable and flexibility.
_____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

                                  Overloading                           vs                          Overriding
                                  
                          Same method name but different                                 Same method name and same
                          parameters                                                     parameters
                          _________________________________________________________________________________________________________
                          Also called                                                    Also called 
                          compile time polymorphism                                      runtime polymorphism
                          ______________________________________________________________________________________________________
                          Return type and scope doesn't matter                           Return type and scope matters
                          ____________________________________________________________________________________________________
                          Happens within a same class or subclass                        Only happens in subclass
                          ______________________________________________________________________________________________________
                          Performance is good                                            Performance is bad
                          ______________________________________________________________________________________________________
                          Static binding is used for overloading                         Dynamic binding is used for overriding
